---
description: When running backend commands, always try to use docker compose commands or the Makefile commands
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

When running commands for the backend, always use either docker compose commands directly or the commands in the Makefile, such as `make docker-dev` to start up the servics, or `make docker-down` to stop all of the services.

When running python commands, always run them through docker using the docker compose web service as the container in which commands run.